PERMITTED
  - Reading and studying the source code
  - Running the software for personal use
  - Modifying the software for your own personal use
    (modified builds must remain private and for yourself only)
  - Copying small snippets of code (10–20 lines or fewer) freely,
    no credit required
  - Forking this repository, provided your fork clearly credits
    the original project and links to https://github.com/sillygru/wispie/

FORBIDDEN
  - Commercial use of this project or any derivative
  - Selling, licensing, or monetizing this project or any modified version
  - Distributing this project publicly, in whole or in substantial part
  - Presenting this project or modified versions as your own work
  - Publishing a modified version as a separate application
  - Copying a whole feature or large self-contained section of code
    without explicit written permission from the author

────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

SNIPPETS
  Small snippets (roughly 10–20 lines or fewer): free to use, no
  credit needed.

  Larger excerpts (a few hundred lines or more): not outright
  forbidden, but please reach out at gru@gru0.dev — feedback on
  what you're building is appreciated.

  Whole features or substantial self-contained sections of code:
  not permitted without explicit written permission.

FORKS
  Public forks are allowed as long as the fork's README clearly
  states it is a fork of Wispie and includes a link to the
  original project: https://github.com/sillygru/wispie/

EXCEPTIONS
  For anything not covered above, or for custom exception permission, contact me at gru@gru0.dev.

